    <dcterms:title>Convicted criminal escapes from Amherst County Courthouse; fire destroys apartment in Martinsville, Va.; Roanoke Valley Citizens Traffic Safety Council recommends safety belts in cars</dcterms:title>
    <dcterms:description>Footage of the second story bathroom window at the Amherst County Courthouse from which Frank James Collins escaped after his conviction of crimes related to a 60-mile car chase; police officers patrol oncoming cars. Firefighters put out a fire that destroyed a six-room apartment and storage shed in Martinsville, Va. A young woman demonstrates the benefits of safety belts, which the Roanoke Valley Citizens Traffic Safety Council recommends to all vehicle owners.</dcterms:description>
